ZH: 我的右手比左手更强壮。
EN: My right hand is stronger than my left hand.

ZH: 请向右转。
EN: Please turn to the right.

ZH: 他的右脚受伤了。
EN: His right foot is injured.

ZH: 她戴着一只戒指在右手上。
EN: She wears a ring on her right hand.

ZH: 这辆车的右边有个划痕。
EN: There is a scratch on the right side of this car.

ZH: 右眼视力比左眼好。
EN: The vision in my right eye is better than my left eye.

ZH: 请右手握住我的手。
EN: Please shake my hand with your right hand.

ZH: 右边是我的书桌。
EN: My desk is on the right side.

ZH: 他挥动右拳打败了对手。
EN: He defeated his opponent by swinging his right fist.

ZH: 我的右肩感到疼痛。
EN: My right shoulder hurts.

ZH: 坐在我右边的那个女生是我的好朋友。
EN: The girl sitting on my right side is my good friend.

ZH: 左转或者右转？
EN: Turn left or turn right?

ZH: 他有个右耳环。
EN: He wears an earring on his right ear.

ZH: 我的右边是窗户。
EN: There is a window on my right side.

ZH: 她是班上右边最聪明的学生。
EN: She is the smartest student on the right side of the class.

ZH: 手表应该戴在右手还是左手？
EN: Should the watch be worn on the right hand or the left hand?

ZH: 右拐会带你到城市中心。
EN: Turning right will take you to the city center.

ZH: 右边的植物需要更多阳光。
EN: The plants on the right side need more sunlight.

ZH: 请用笔把正确答案圈在右边。
EN: Please circle the correct answer on the right side with a pen.

ZH: 右腕扭伤了。
EN: My right wrist is sprained.
